    <note>Wang(2) Yuan(2) [7385] He used his uncle Zhi's [7079] yin to enter the civil service. Dan's [8153] grandson, Lun(2)'s [8178] grandfather, Yi(5)'s [7377] father, Chao(2) Zhongyan's [7119] son-in-law. Since his first wife, Zhao(1) Anren's [8176] granddaughter, died at the age of 30 in 1063, his second wife Chao(2) Shi was no less than 22 years old when they married. Zhao(1) Shi produced six sons, but apparently no daughters before she died. His son-in-law, Huangfu(1) Shen [3423], had the same generational name as the son of Huangfu(1) Bi [868]. His son-in-law, Li(2) Shimou [3527], had the same generational name as the grandsons of Li(2) Zhaoshu [987]. Chao Buzhi, WJ, 67.10a-13a, 13a-14a (wife #1, born Zhao, who married him at age 16 and died in 1063 at age 30), 14a-15a (wife #2, born Chao, who died in 1093 at age 53). CBD, 1, 104.</note>
